        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 5 at 6:13PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 611 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Denton, moving east at 30 mph. In addition to lightning and brief
heavy rainfall, wind gusts to 40 mph and hail up to one half inch in
diameter is possible with this storm.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Denton, Winifred, Danvers, Suffolk, Hilger, and Christina.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for
central Montana.</instruction>
